703069f-a.text:
Atlantic Ave., at the N.W. corner of Wyona Street (Wyckoff Street), showing what was the M. E. Sackman home in 1873. C. Boulton had his Stationery store here at a later date. The structure still stands in (1936).
About 1885.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

703070f-a.text:
Atlantic Ave., east from and including Wyona Street. The view shows the Long Island Railroad Structure. A frame building is at 2719 Atlantic Ave., at the N.E. corner of Wyona Street.
July 27, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
